<p><br><strong>Inspection</strong><br>A digital exam is often followed by a digital inspection of said exam. If you want UvA-laptops and technical support staff on location during the inspection, you'll have to contact your programme coordinator at least 8 weeks prior. Would you rather organise the inspection on your own? Learn everything about inspections in Ans <a href="https://canvas.uva.nl/courses/45162/pages/tools-ans-inspection">here</a>.</p><p><br><strong>Surveillance</strong><br>Does your exam have more than 50 students and have you not requested additional surveillance yet? Please send a mail with a request for surveillance to <b><a href="tentamenvoorziening-sw@uva.nl">tentamenvoorziening-sw@uva.nl</a></b> as soon as possible. The Examinations Board has
  established the following guideluines regarding the number of surveillants to
  be present during an exam:
</p><ul>
  <li>&lt;50 candidates: 1 or more surveillant(s)</li>
  <li>50-150 candidates: 2 or more surveillants</li>
  <li>for every 75 candidates on top of this: 1 more surveillant</li>
</ul> <br>Questions? <a href="https://outlook.office365.com/book/ICTOSocialSciences@Amsuni.onmicrosoft.com/">Schedule an appointment</a> with the ICTO team or send us an e-mail at <a href="mailto:icto-csw@uva.nl">icto-csw@uva.nl</a>. <b>For questions regarding surveillance, please contact tentamenvoorzieningen-sw</b> via the e-mail address above.<br><br>Kind regards,<br>The ICTO-team Social Sciences<br><br><br><br><em>This is an automated e-mail. Feel free to contact us in case of questions or suggestions.</em><p></p>